You’re right—the expected screen has **no white gutter around the right illustration**. The green panel should touch the right and bottom edges of the viewport.

The gap is usually caused by padding/margin on `.screen`, `.content-container`, or a parent wrapper. Keep the padding only inside `.left-content` and `.page-header`.

Use this layout:

```css
html,
body {
    margin: 0;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 100%;
}

body {
    overflow-x: hidden;
}

.screen {
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 100vh;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    max-width: none;
}

.content-container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 57%) minmax(0, 43%);

    width: 100%;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 96px);

    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    gap: 0;
}
```

Keep spacing inside only the left column:

```css
.left-content {
    width: 100%;
    min-width: 0;

    padding:
        clamp(40px, 7vh, 72px)
        clamp(32px, 5vw, 96px);

    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
}
```

Make the illustration fill its entire grid cell:

```css
.right-illustration {
    position: relative;

    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 96px);

    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;

    overflow: hidden;
    border-top-left-radius: 40px;
    background-color: var(--color-green-dark);
}
```

The pattern must also cover the whole panel:

```css
.background-pattern {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;

    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;

    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;

    margin: 0;
    z-index: 1;
}
```

Also check that you do **not** have any of these active:

```css
.screen {
    padding: ...;
    max-width: ...;
    margin: auto;
}

.content-container {
    gap: ...;
    padding: ...;
    max-width: ...;
    margin: auto;
}

.right-illustration {
    margin-right: ...;
}
```

For your expected layout, `gap` must be exactly:

```css
gap: 0;
```

The header can still have horizontal padding:

```css
.page-header {
    height: 96px;
    padding: 16px clamp(24px, 7vw, 140px);
}
```

That padding should not be applied to `.content-container`. This will make the green panel flush with the right and bottom edges while preserving the white header area above it.
